      "message": "Logged-in `/login?next\u003d/redfish/v1/...` users are sent to `/`, not the Redfish target.\nthe stated goal is to preserve Redfish redirects. \n\nRecommended fix: `if to.path \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027/login\u0027` and the user is already logged in, inspect the same next target and redirect to it when it is a safe Redfish path:\n```\nfunction allowRouterToNavigate(to, next, currentUserRole) {\n  if (to.path \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027/login\u0027 \u0026\u0026 store.getters[\u0027authentication/isLoggedIn\u0027]) {\n    next(\u0027/\u0027);\n    return;\n  }\n```",
